Homepage: https://github.com/example/dawnstar-readaloud
Description: Text-to-Speech application with neural voices
 Dawnstar ReadAloud is a lightweight Text-to-Speech (TTS) command-line
 application that reads text from files, PDFs, EPUBs, URLs, or direct input.
 .
 Features:
  - Multiple TTS engines: Edge TTS (neural voices), gTTS, eSpeak
  - Multi-language support: US English, UK English, Tamil
  - Smart caching for faster repeated playback
  - Global keyboard shortcuts for reading selected text
  - Document processing: skips front matter in EPUBs/PDFs
  - Optional daemon mode for low-latency speech synthesis
  - Desktop notifications and progress indicators
 .
 For best quality neural voices, install edge-tts via pip:
   pip3 install --user edge-tts
